Anheuser-Busch Cos' Metal ContainerCorp said it plans to build a beverage can manufacturing plantat Chester, N.Y.    The facility is expected to become operational in late1988.    Metal Container operates six can and lid plants in theU.S., and plans to build three more, including the Chesterfacility. Facilities are under construction at Windsor, Colo.,and Riverside, Calif.    The Anheuser-Busch unit said it expects to produce sixbillion cans and eight billion lids in 1987. Reuter&#3;